### Dataplane Enhancement Taxonomy
* **Presentation**: [02) Dataplane Enhancement Taxonomy](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-detnet-02-dataplane-enhancement-taxonomy-01)
* **Draft**: [draft-ietf-detnet-dataplane-taxonomy](https://datatracker.ietf.org/draft-ietf-detnet-dataplane-taxonomy/)
* **Presented by**: Jeong-dong Ryoo
* **Discussion**:
  * Section 8 (Considerations for Interoperability between Solutions) has been revised to reference [draft-ietf-detnet-multi-domain-framework](https://datatracker.ietf.org/draft-ietf-detnet-multi-domain-framework/). Interoperability levels are analyzed on the control plane (operability) and data plane (performance metrics).
  * Mike Johnston asked how an implementer should interpret "low, medium, or high" interoperability levels. Jeong-dong Ryoo responded that this is an informational document aimed at categorization rather than providing specific implementation specifications.
  * Lou Berger invited further contributions on the mailing list to improve the interoperability definitions.

