### On-time Forwarding with Non-Work Conserving Stateless Core Fair Queuing
* **Presentation**: [10) On-time Forwarding with Non-Work Conserving Stateless Core Fair Queuing](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-detnet-10-on-time-forwarding-with-non-work-conserving-stateless-core-fair-queuing-00)
* **Draft**: [draft-ietf-detnet-nscore](https://datatracker.ietf.org/draft-ietf-detnet-nscore/)
* **Presented by**: Yunchao Liu
* **Discussion**:
  * Revision 02 introduces an "arrival-based" eligibility time (ET) and finish time (FT) calculation method (Section 5.2.2). This method uses local arrival time, scheduling gap, and a delay component in the packet header, eliminating the need for strict synchronization or propagation delay awareness.
  * The solution has been implemented on FPGA and is currently undergoing performance testing.

